description:
Starting in 1998 thisshort-livedseries from Chaos comics wasn't much loved or noticed when it was first published compared to its higher profile characters. But as it turns out it was in fact a very important piece of Chaos universe law. The Omen introduced many new characters, and tied in minor existing ones, to the Chaos universe and set in motion the gathering of the roster ofmajorplayers in a story arc that will be concluded in the epic Armageddon series. the issues start with 20months till the end and ends with 16months till the end.
It is worth noting that the next issue in the count down to Armageddon is Vexed with 15 months till the end.
name: The Omen

description:
One shot Graphic novel from the British team-up of writer Alan Moore and artist Brian Bolland.

In the story, for the first time the Joker's origin is revealed in this tale of insanity and human perseverance. Looking to prove that any man can be pushed past his breaking point and go mad, the Joker attempts to drive Commissioner Gordon insane. After shooting and permanently paralyzing his daughter Barbara (a.k.a. Batgirl), the Joker kidnaps the commissioner and attacks his mind in hopes of breaking the man. But refusing to give up, Gordon maintains his sanity with the help of Batman in an effort to best the madman.

The book became one of the most famous and popular Batman tales of the revisionist 1980's era and remains so to this day.There exist over 14 different printings of this edition with various small changes to the cover.

In 2008, DC released Batman: The Killing Joke Deluxe Edition featuring new coloring from Brian Bolland.

Collected Editions:

  • DC Universe: The Stories of Alan Moore (2006)
name: Batman: The Killing Joke

description:
The Twelve Volume 1

During World War II, several heroes were captured by the Nazis and cryogenically frozen, to be experimented on later. The year is now 2008, and the heroes are found and revived, they are the Twelve.

The series had been put on hold after issue 8 in december 2008, after a falling out between the writer of the comic, J.M. Straczynski and then editor in chief of Marvel Comics, Joe Quasada.

The series briefly returned with a one-shot in 2010 named The Twelve: Spearhead, written and drawn by the original penciler of the series. In 2012, the series finally continued publication, with the original artist and writer as the creative team, finishing the 12 part story.

Collected Editions

  • The Twelve HC (#1-12)
  • The Twelve vol. 1 (#1-6)
  • The Twelve vol. 2 (#7-12)

Translated into Spanish.
name: The Twelve
